      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ok, I wanted to avoid memory-ordering related issues by performing the thread self check first, but I\u0027ve performed a more in-deep analysis, and came to the conclusion that this will not work, even trying to use atomic operations on the qemu_global_lock_held doesn\u0027t get rid of all possible data races because there is no way to atomically compare a QemuThread value at the moment. I\u0027m uploading a new implementation that uses a __thread boolean instead which seems to work well and is 100% reliable. Testing doesn\u0027t show performance differences with 3DMark. Oh my.",
